<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,403,546]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,292,403,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Discussion:</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ozdikmen" box="[300,508,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="33" refString="Ozdikmen, H. (2006) Necessary changes of names in Hydrachnellae (Arachnida: Acari). Munis Entomology &amp; Zoology, 1, 51 - 54." type="journal article" year="2006">
Ã–zdikmen (
<number box="[438,500,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="2006.0">2006</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
proposed 
<emphasis box="[631,744,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Acerbitas</emphasis>
as a new name for the junior homonym 
<taxonomicName authority="Koch 1836" authorityName="Koch" authorityYear="1836" box="[1221,1432,404,430]" class="Arachnida" family="Thyasidae" genus="Thyas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1221,1291,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Thyas</emphasis>
Koch 
<number box="[1370,1432,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1836.0">1836</number>
</taxonomicName>
. Following the rules of the International Code for Zoological Nomenclature, the oldest available valid name for the genus is 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook, 1974" authorityName="Cook" authorityYear="1974" box="[344,616,481,507]" class="Arachnida" family="Hydryphantidae" genus="Todothyas" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,462,481,506]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Todothyas</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[473,616,481,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="31" refString="Cook, D. R. (1974) Water mite genera and subgenera. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 21, V + 1 - 860." type="journal article" year="1974">
Cook, 
<number box="[553,616,481,507]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" value="1974.0">1974</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, 
<emphasis box="[761,875,481,506]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Acerbitas</emphasis>
becomes a valid name for the subgenus which includes all the described species grouped in the former subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[927,997,520,545]" class="Arachnida" family="Thyasidae" genus="Thyas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[927,997,520,545]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Thyas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
